premise_source_doc_sentence: These chronological `` eras '' describe different phases of Seagal 's career , and include the `` Golden Era ''  (  1988-1991  )  , the period of Seagal 's first successes , the `` Silver Era ''  (  1992-1997  )  , during which Seagal saw the peak of his fame and made high-profile blockbusters , a `` Transitional Period ''  (  1998-2002  )  during which he made lower-profile or ensemble films , a lengthy `` direct-to-video '' period  (  his most prolific to date , 2003-2008  )  and , in the 2012 updated addition , a `` Chief Seagal '' period  (  2009 -- Present  )  during which Seagal moved into television and began reflecting elements of his Steven Seagal : Lawman persona in his films
